---
name: test-repair
description: Fix failing tests with the smallest safe code or test change.
---

## Purpose
Repair broken tests or test setup so the suite passes again.

## When to Use
- When tests fail after a code change.
- When test fixtures, mocks, or expectations drift.
- When you need to restore green status quickly.

## Workflow
1. Reproduce the failure and isolate the root cause.
2. Fix the smallest layer that caused the break.
3. Re-run the affected tests or explain the verification path.

## Guardrails
- Do not mask product bugs with weaker tests.
- Do not widen assertions unless the behavior truly changed.
- Prefer minimal fixture or expectation updates.

## Output
- The root cause and fix.
- Files changed.
- The tests verified or still needed.